Class AbstractDeNormaliser

java.lang.Object
  au.gov.naa.digipres.xena.kernel.normalise.AbstractDeNormaliser
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
BinaryDeNormaliser, XmlDeNormaliser
public abstract class AbstractDeNormaliser
extends java.lang.Object
implements javax.xml.transform.sax.TransformerHandler

AbstractDeNormaliser is an empty implementation of TransformerHandler that is able to be overridden to De-Normalise Xena files. It contains a several denoramliser specific abstract methods that must be implemented by any new denormaliser.

getOutputFileExtension

public java.lang.String getOutputFileExtension(XenaInputSource xis)
                                        throws XenaException
Return the file extension which should be used for the file exported by this denormaliser. This default method just returns the extension associated with the type associated with this denormaliser, but concrete classes may need to determine the extension from the file being denormalised, as some denormalisers can produce multiple file types (eg an office normalised file could be a word processor file, a spreadsheet or a presentation).

output file extension
